validateEmailUser

public static User validateEmailUser(java.lang.String aAddress)
                              throws DatabaseException,
                                     java.io.IOException
This method validates user by its email address/login, in DB or as unix user by ypmatch. IF address valid in DB, then it returns the corresponding User Object. ELSE IF address valid transbit unix address(ypmatch), then it returns the corresponding User Object, else return null. ELSE return a new External User object.

Parameters:
aAddress - Users's email/login to be validated
Throws:
DatabaseException
IOExcepiton
java.io.IOException
